  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 210°C/ 190°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to one side of a large baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629108433913-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629108433913-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629108433913-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629108433913-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629108433913-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> meat-free sausages </strong>to the other side of the tray</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until the sausages are cooked through and the chips are golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629108437407-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629108437407-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629108437407-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629108437407-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629108437407-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>cannellini beans</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained cannellini beans</strong> to the pot with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp] </span>sugar</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened then remove from the heat and set aside – these are your <strong>homemade beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1694071190279-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1694071190279-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1694071190279-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
